    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mount Vernon May Limit All-Night Retailers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Robert Worth</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Worth, Robert</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Police Comr Gertrude Laforgia of Mount Vernon, NY, asks City Council to pass law requiring 24-hour retail stores to close between midnight and 5 AM (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Mount Vernon police commissioner, Gertrude Laforgia, has asked the City Council to pass a law requiring retail businesses that are now open all night to close between midnight and 5 a.m.</p>
        <p>In a letter to council members, she said the police responded frequently to complaints about noise, loitering, assaults, robberies and weapons possession outside three all-night delicatessens on Third Street. One site drew 67 police calls  in 1999, she said, always between midnight and 5 a.m.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Mount Vernon police commissioner, Gertrude Laforgia, has asked the City Council to pass a law requiring retail businesses that are now open all night to close between midnight and 5 a.m.</p>
        <p>In a letter to council members, she said the police responded frequently to complaints about noise, loitering, assaults, robberies and weapons possession outside three all-night delicatessens on Third Street. One site drew 67 police calls  in 1999, she said, always between midnight and 5 a.m.</p>
        <p>Ruth Hassell-Thompson, the City Council president, said that the council had been working with the commissioner on the problem, and that a law would be passed. ''It is proven to be a serious nuisance factor to the neighborhood,'' she added.</p>
        <p>Robert Worth</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
